# SoundGrabber

SoundGrabber is an audio recording utility for macOS that allows you to capture system audio.

## Purchase

SoundGrabber is available for purchase at [your store link]. While the source code is freely available under GPL, the compiled application requires a purchase to support ongoing development.

## Installation

1. Purchase and download SoundGrabber.app.zip
2. Unzip the file
3. Right-click (or Control-click) SoundGrabber.app and select "Open"
4. Click "Open" in the security dialog that appears
5. SoundGrabber will automatically check for required components:
   - If BlackHole is not installed, you'll be prompted to install it
   - If SwitchAudioSource is not installed, it will be installed automatically
6. Follow any installer prompts that appear
7. Restart your Mac after BlackHole installation (recommended)

## Usage

1. Click the SoundGrabber icon in your menu bar
2. Select "Start Recording" to begin capturing audio
3. Select "Stop Recording" when finished
4. Recordings are saved to your Desktop by default

## Requirements

- macOS 10.15 or later
- Microphone permissions (will be requested on first use)
- Administrator password may be required for component installation

